parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors and brake lock-up can cause loss of control, accidents, and extended stopping distances, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Warped rotors
brakes that lock up when first applied
especially in wet or damp conditions
and extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder failure can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and loss of control.
symptoms: Leaky master cylinder
brakes not working properly
and failure to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS malfunction can cause the brakes to fail to respond, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and loss of control.
symptoms: ABS brakes fail to engage
extended stopping distances
and brakes that are hard to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pull can cause loss of control, accidents, and extended stopping distances, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle pulls to the left or right when braking
unpredictable direction prior to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can reduce visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers work erratically
shutting on and off on their own
failing to operate when needed
or only working intermittently in low or high speed settings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause the wipers to stop working altogether, reducing visibility during rain or snow and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wiper motor only works intermittently
despite reconnecting the switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise coming from the rear window can be a distraction to the driver and may indicate a more serious issue with the window's seal or mechanism.
symptoms: Unusual noise coming from the rear window
even when the window is sealed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door seal can cause air and water leaks, leading to discomfort, noise, and potential water damage to the vehicle's interior.
symptoms: Air leaks from the door
water enters the vehicle through the door
noise or rattling from the door area
door panel makes noise.
